  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "The Caltech Pedestrian Detection Benchmark is one of the largest-scale pedestrian databases [85].",
    "It was captured using onboard vehicle cameras over approximately 10 hours.",
    "The video resolution is 640x480 pixels at 30 frames per second.",
    "It includes annotations for approximately 250,000 frames (about 137 minutes), 350,000 bounding boxes, and 2,300 pedestrians.",
    "It also provides annotations for the temporal correspondence between bounding boxes and occlusions.The INRIA personnel dataset is one of the most widely used static pedestrian detection databases [3]."
  ],
